## Limitations

This report is based on available data and expert opinions up to October 2023. The rapidly evolving nature of climate science means that new findings could alter current understandings. Additionally, the complexity of climate systems and their interactions with agricultural practices means that predictions are subject to uncertainties. Further research is needed to refine these predictions and develop adaptive strategies for mitigating the impacts of climate change on food supply.

